WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.069 --> 00:00:06.500
In the Game of Thrones TV show, Euron Greyjoy
is a violent shit-talking pirate who wants

00:00:06.500 --> 00:00:08.500
to “fuck the queen” and rule the world.

00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:14.780
But in the book series, Euron’s a totally
different character – he’s a scary manipulative

00:00:14.780 --> 00:00:21.420
murderer, a charismatic politician, and a
psychedelic sorcerer hungry for apocalyptic

00:00:21.420 --> 00:00:22.420
power.

00:00:22.420 --> 00:00:27.539
He’s got a magic dragon horn, and warlock
“slaves”, and Valyrian steel armour.

00:00:27.539 --> 00:00:33.390
He’s connected to the mysterious magic of
Bloodraven, the Faceless Men, and Valyria.

00:00:33.390 --> 00:00:39.600
Euron doesn’t just want a throne, he wants
cosmic eldritch power, and plans a blasphemous

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:43.860
blood sacrifice to make himself a Lovecraftian
god.

00:00:43.860 --> 00:00:48.739
The fan community, especially Poor Quentyn,
theorise that Euron will bring apocalypse

00:00:48.739 --> 00:00:50.110
to Westeros.

00:00:50.110 --> 00:00:55.190
At the start of the story, Balon Greyjoy rules
the Iron Islands.

00:00:55.190 --> 00:00:59.620
He rebels against the Iron Throne, and declares
the Islands his own separate kingdom – his

00:00:59.620 --> 00:01:03.359
daughter Asha and his son Theon attack the
north.

00:01:03.359 --> 00:01:06.070
Balon also has three brothers.

00:01:06.070 --> 00:01:11.930
Victarion is a warrior – he’s strong and
loyal and kinda stupid . Aeron is a priest

00:01:11.930 --> 00:01:13.040
of the Drowned God.

00:01:13.040 --> 00:01:17.240
He used to be a party boy, until he was born
again as a religious man.

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:20.100
And then there’s Euron Crow’s Eye.

00:01:20.100 --> 00:01:24.630
Euron was exiled from the Islands years ago,
and has since been sailing far-distant seas

00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:30.670
in his infamous pirate ship, the Silence – its
crew are mutes, with their tongues ripped

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:31.670
out.

00:01:31.670 --> 00:01:36.630
Its sails are black, and its decks are painted
red to hide the blood that soaks them.

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:40.659
The Silence is feared all across the east,
from Ib to Asshai.

00:01:40.659 --> 00:01:45.600
But Euron doesn’t appear in the story right
away – he’s introduced slowly, like the

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:50.800
monster in a horror movie, with just rumours
and memories to build tension and mystery

00:01:50.800 --> 00:01:55.119
– “men say terrible things” of Euron
Greyjoy.

00:01:55.119 --> 00:02:01.391
Victarion and Aeron hate and fear Euron – Aeron
thinks “the storm is coming”, “and its

00:02:01.391 --> 00:02:04.790
name is Euron Crow’s Eye”.

00:02:04.790 --> 00:02:10.700
In Book 3, King Balon suddenly dies – he
falls to his death from a bridge on Pyke.

00:02:10.700 --> 00:02:16.280
And the very next day, Euron returns after
years away, and claims Balon’s throne.

00:02:16.280 --> 00:02:20.400
It’s very suspicious, so Asha thinks that
Euron murdered Balon.

00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:25.780
In the TV show, Euron does straight up murder
Balon, but in the books it’s more complicated.

00:02:25.780 --> 00:02:30.860
Arya meets a witch called “the ghost of
High Heart”, who makes a bunch of accurate

00:02:30.860 --> 00:02:32.780
predictions and prophecies.

00:02:32.780 --> 00:02:37.880
And the witch sees “a man without a face”
on a bridge that sways and swings.

00:02:37.880 --> 00:02:43.080
On his shoulder perches “a drowned crow
with seaweed hanging from his wings”.

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:48.380
Presumably, the “man without a face” is
an assassin of the Faceless Men, and the “drowned

00:02:48.380 --> 00:02:54.810
crow” is Euron “Crow’s Eye” – meaning
that Euron hired a Faceless Man to kill Balon.

00:02:54.810 --> 00:02:59.900
Hiring a Faceless assassin is expensive, especially
if the target is an important person, like

00:02:59.900 --> 00:03:00.900
King Balon.

00:03:00.900 --> 00:03:05.300
But it’s implied that you can pay the Faceless
Men with something other than money, if you

00:03:05.300 --> 00:03:08.530
sacrifice something that’s important to
you.

00:03:08.530 --> 00:03:11.610
Euron claims that he once had a dragon egg.

00:03:11.610 --> 00:03:16.240
He tried to make it hatch, but got frustrated,
and threw the egg in the sea.

00:03:16.240 --> 00:03:22.020
Dragon eggs are super valuable and rare, so
would Euron really throw one away?

00:03:22.020 --> 00:03:26.730
Some fans believe that Euron actually gave
the egg to the Faceless Men as payment – so

00:03:26.730 --> 00:03:30.210
that they would throw Balon in the sea.

00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:36.120
One way or another, Euron secretly hired a
magical assassin to murder his own brother.

00:03:36.120 --> 00:03:40.600
But publicly, he hides his evil behind a charismatic
persona.

00:03:40.600 --> 00:03:45.250
The real Euron is “hidden”, which is symbolised
by Euron’s eyepatch.

00:03:45.250 --> 00:03:50.920
His right eye is described as his “smiling
eye”, the charming, swaggering, magnanimous

00:03:50.920 --> 00:03:51.920
side.

00:03:51.920 --> 00:03:56.330
But the eye behind his eyepatch is his “blood
eye”, where he hides his full cruelty and

00:03:56.330 --> 00:03:58.540
sorcery and ambition.

00:03:58.540 --> 00:04:03.980
By the time the ironborn see Euron’s true
face, it’s too late.

00:04:03.980 --> 00:04:08.950
After King Balon dies, the ironborn hold a
“kingsmoot” to choose a new king.

00:04:08.950 --> 00:04:13.750
And Euron uses a combination of politics,
murder, and swag[yolo] to win the [driftwood]

00:04:13.750 --> 00:04:14.750
crown.

00:04:14.750 --> 00:04:19.380
He rolls up in his infamous ship the Silence,
with an entourage of “mutes”, “monsters”

00:04:19.380 --> 00:04:21.120
and “wizards” from the east.

00:04:21.120 --> 00:04:26.840
He hands out treasure from his years of piracy,
bribing some rivals , and murdering others.

00:04:26.840 --> 00:04:32.290
He makes grandiose speeches about how badass
he is – how he’s raided, raped and looted

00:04:32.290 --> 00:04:36.110
all over the world , which is the kind of
thing the ironborn respect [as qualifications

00:04:36.110 --> 00:04:37.110
for office].

00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:41.390
In his election speech, Euron says he’ll
make the Iron Islands great again, evoking

00:04:41.390 --> 00:04:43.680
their glorious past as “conquerors”.

00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:49.740
He shows off his magic horn, Dragonbinder,
and says it has the power to bind dragons

00:04:49.740 --> 00:04:51.280
to his will.

00:04:51.280 --> 00:04:57.460
Euron plans to sail across the world to Meereen,
and to steal Daenerys Targaryen’s dragons,

00:04:57.460 --> 00:04:59.980
and use them to take over Westeros.

00:04:59.980 --> 00:05:06.620
It’s a totally crazy plan, so naturally
the ironborn love it, and make Euron their

00:05:06.620 --> 00:05:07.620
king.

00:05:07.620 --> 00:05:11.960
Euron leads the ironborn to conquer some nearby
islands, cementing his power by giving them

00:05:11.960 --> 00:05:12.990
some glory.

00:05:12.990 --> 00:05:18.400
But privately, Euron doesn’t care about
these islands, or the ironborn – he cares

00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:23.460
only about himself, and everyone else is just
a means to an end.

00:05:23.460 --> 00:05:27.510
Euron wants “The world”, he wants dragons
and “Woe”.

00:05:27.510 --> 00:05:32.680
And he wants to marry Daenerys – “When
the kraken weds the dragon … let all the

00:05:32.680 --> 00:05:34.550
world beware”.

00:05:34.550 --> 00:05:38.930
So Euron sends his brother Victarion with
Dragonbinder to fetch Daenerys.

00:05:38.930 --> 00:05:44.060
Victarion hates Euron because years ago, Euron
had sex with Victarion’s wife.

00:05:44.060 --> 00:05:50.370
Then, because of Victarion’s fucked-up male
pride, Victarion beat his wife to death – this

00:05:50.370 --> 00:05:52.530
is why Euron was exiled.

00:05:52.530 --> 00:05:58.840
So Victarion agrees to sail east, but he secretly
plans to take Daenerys for himself, as revenge

00:05:58.840 --> 00:06:00.790
for Euron taking his wife.

00:06:00.790 --> 00:06:07.670
But Euron knows all about Victarion’s resentment,
and he exploits these feelings to manipulate

00:06:07.670 --> 00:06:08.670
Victarion.

00:06:08.670 --> 00:06:13.590
Victarion’s like a “puppet” – “blind
to the tentacles that grasp” him.

00:06:13.590 --> 00:06:16.160
So he’ll probably fail to outsmart Euron.

00:06:16.160 --> 00:06:21.091
We’re told that Dragonbinder brings dragons
not the person who blows the horn, but to

00:06:21.091 --> 00:06:25.730
the horn’s true “master” – and Euron
is the master here.

00:06:25.730 --> 00:06:30.360
So one way or another, it looks likely that
Victarion will die so that Euron can get at

00:06:30.360 --> 00:06:35.080
Daenerys – Euron might steal the dragon
Viserion, like the Night King does in the

00:06:35.080 --> 00:06:36.460
TV show.

00:06:36.460 --> 00:06:41.660
So this is how Euron operates – he exploits
peoples’ hopes and fears to make them his

00:06:41.660 --> 00:06:45.520
slaves in his quest for power and woe.

00:06:45.520 --> 00:06:52.560
Euron uses and abuses his family, and his
people – and now he wants the world.

00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:59.100
But how did Euron Greyjoy, an ironborn reaver,
become obsessed with dragons and world domination?

00:06:59.100 --> 00:07:02.650
How did Euron become the “Crow’s Eye”?

00:07:02.650 --> 00:07:06.690
Euron says that when he was a boy, he dreamed
that he could fly.

00:07:06.690 --> 00:07:09.210
When he woke, his maester said he couldn’t
fly.

00:07:09.210 --> 00:07:11.000
But what if he lied?

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:12.320
Maybe we all can fly.

00:07:12.320 --> 00:07:17.120
“How will we … know unless we leap from
some tall tower?”.

00:07:17.120 --> 00:07:21.590
This story is almost identical to how Bran
Stark discovers magic.

00:07:21.590 --> 00:07:24.710
When Bran is a boy, he falls from a tall tower.

00:07:24.710 --> 00:07:30.860
Then he dreams that he can fly – the “three-eyed
crow” visits his dream, and opens Bran’s

00:07:30.860 --> 00:07:33.360
third eye to his magic.

00:07:33.360 --> 00:07:37.830
When Bran wakes up, he can’t fly, his maester
says he can’t learn magic.

00:07:37.830 --> 00:07:43.380
But the maester is wrong, and Bran learns
magic from the three-eyed crow, aka Bloodraven,

00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:46.390
who is way creepier in the books.

00:07:46.390 --> 00:07:52.120
So these flying dream stories are too similar
to be a coincidence – Bloodraven is called

00:07:52.120 --> 00:07:57.120
three-eyed crow, and Euron is called the Crow’s
Eye.

00:07:57.120 --> 00:08:03.669
Bloodraven has “one red eye”, and Euron’s
sigil is one red eye, with crows.

00:08:03.669 --> 00:08:09.389
So the theory goes that Euron, like Bran,
was visited in his dreams by the three-eyed

00:08:09.389 --> 00:08:10.389
crow.

00:08:10.389 --> 00:08:14.110
In Bran’s dream, he sees “the bones of
a thousand other dreamers”.

00:08:14.110 --> 00:08:18.760
So it looks like Bloodraven has tried out
a bunch of potential students, but most failed

00:08:18.760 --> 00:08:20.080
or died.

00:08:20.080 --> 00:08:22.670
Maybe Euron was one of those students.

00:08:22.670 --> 00:08:28.300
Maybe when Bloodraven visited Euron’s dreams,
he saw how crazy and cruel Euron is, and decided

00:08:28.300 --> 00:08:30.389
not to teach him magic.

00:08:30.389 --> 00:08:36.580
But the damage was done – Euron went rogue
with his third eye opened.

00:08:36.580 --> 00:08:42.289
Bloodraven and Bran are greenseers, with the
power to skinchange – to enter the mind

00:08:42.289 --> 00:08:43.880
of another creature.

00:08:43.880 --> 00:08:48.070
We don’t know if Euron has that power, but
it would make sense if he did.

00:08:48.070 --> 00:08:53.620
Cause Euron gives Victarion a mute “dusky
woman” to go east with him, and fans speculate

00:08:53.620 --> 00:08:58.980
that she’s spying for Euron – like maybe
Euron is skinchanging into her from afar,

00:08:58.980 --> 00:09:01.650
to see what Victarion’s up to.

00:09:01.650 --> 00:09:06.930
Skinchanging a human is seen as an evil abominable
act – so it’s exactly the sort of thing

00:09:06.930 --> 00:09:09.150
Euron might do.

00:09:09.150 --> 00:09:13.920
Skinchanging might also explain how Euron
controls his mute crew on the Silence – like,

00:09:13.920 --> 00:09:18.319
how else could you co-ordinate the crew of
a ship if they can’t talk?

00:09:18.319 --> 00:09:22.570
And skinchanging isn’t just a Stark thing
– we’re told that some ironborn skinchange

00:09:22.570 --> 00:09:24.310
into sea creatures.

00:09:24.310 --> 00:09:27.950
So Euron might just be a skinchanger.

00:09:27.950 --> 00:09:33.150
Bran and Bloodraven can also magically enter
peoples’ dreams – and after Euron says

00:09:33.150 --> 00:09:38.190
he’ll marry Daenerys, Daenerys has a creepy
sex dream of a man with “blue” “bruised”

00:09:38.190 --> 00:09:44.240
lips – Euron has blue bruised lips because
of a drug he takes, so that’s probably him

00:09:44.240 --> 00:09:45.880
in her dream.

00:09:45.880 --> 00:09:49.540
Euron also enters Aeron’s dream, later on.

00:09:49.540 --> 00:09:55.610
So it’s just speculation, but Euron might
secretly have the magic powers of a greenseer.

00:09:55.610 --> 00:10:00.680
Either way, a visit from the three-eye crow
could explain Euron’s motivations.

00:10:00.680 --> 00:10:05.210
In Bran’s flying dream, he sees “The whole
world” “spread out below him” – he

00:10:05.210 --> 00:10:09.740
sees Winterfell and Asshai, sees dragons,
and “the heart of winter”.

00:10:09.740 --> 00:10:14.930
Maybe Euron saw the same things – and when
he saw dragons and magic and the whole world

00:10:14.930 --> 00:10:18.950
spread below him, he wanted it all.

00:10:18.950 --> 00:10:26.360
Euron tasted godlike magic power, and will
stop at nothing to get more.

00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:31.100
Euron travels to some of the most magic and
mysterious places in the world.

00:10:31.100 --> 00:10:36.180
He says he “sailed to Asshai by the Shadow”,
right at the edge of the map, and saw “wonders

00:10:36.180 --> 00:10:38.970
and terrors beyond imagining”.

00:10:38.970 --> 00:10:43.430
Lots of the most powerful sorcerers in the
story learned magic in Asshai – Melisandre,

00:10:43.430 --> 00:10:46.200
Quaithe, Marwyn, Mirri Maz Duur.

00:10:46.200 --> 00:10:52.010
Asshai is like Hogwarts for edgelords – full
of “shadowbinders” and “bloodmages”

00:10:52.010 --> 00:10:54.570
casting dark spells in the night”.

00:10:54.570 --> 00:11:00.120
And right by Asshai is Stygai, the mysterious
“heart of darkness” where even shadowbinders

00:11:00.120 --> 00:11:06.680
fear to tread – maybe Euron dared to enter
the “corpse city”, and found some evil

00:11:06.680 --> 00:11:08.300
power there.

00:11:08.300 --> 00:11:14.220
Euron also says he sailed to Valyria – the
smoking demon-haunted ruins of the ancient

00:11:14.220 --> 00:11:15.270
dragonlords.

00:11:15.270 --> 00:11:20.550
People say it’s impossible to visit Valyria
and survive, but Euron does have that Valyrian

00:11:20.550 --> 00:11:23.130
steel armour and that Valyrian horn.

00:11:23.130 --> 00:11:28.880
The old Valyrian empire used dragons and slavery
to conquer the world – which might have

00:11:28.880 --> 00:11:31.840
inspired Euron to do the same thing.

00:11:31.840 --> 00:11:37.779
So it seems that after Euron dreamed he could
fly, he travelled the world in search of magic

00:11:37.779 --> 00:11:40.790
power, and developed his ambitions for world
domination.

00:11:40.790 --> 00:11:44.750
And at some point, Euron captured some warlocks
from Qarth.

00:11:44.750 --> 00:11:48.420
The warlocks had just been defeated by Daenerys,
and they were out to get revenge.

00:11:48.420 --> 00:11:53.050
But Euron captured them, and took their shade
of the evening.

00:11:53.050 --> 00:11:58.020
Shade of the evening is a psychedelic drug,
that gives visions of pasts and futures.

00:11:58.020 --> 00:12:03.910
Euron gets really into the shade, to the point
where it stains his lips blue and bruised.

00:12:03.910 --> 00:12:08.950
Euron says the shade opens his eyes, that
there’s “more truth in it than all the

00:12:08.950 --> 00:12:11.060
gods of earth”.

00:12:11.060 --> 00:12:16.520
Euron believes that gods and morality are
lies – and he commits horrific crimes just

00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:19.209
to prove that no god can stop him.

00:12:19.209 --> 00:12:24.450
It’s revealed that Euron murdered three
of his own brothers – as well as Balon,

00:12:24.450 --> 00:12:27.810
he killed Harlon and Robin Greyjoy when they
were young.

00:12:27.810 --> 00:12:31.810
The ironborn see kinslaying as the most evil
crime.

00:12:31.810 --> 00:12:36.650
So after Euron choked the life from Harlon,
he “pissed into the sea”, waiting for

00:12:36.650 --> 00:12:40.390
a god to strike him down, and “None did”.

00:12:40.390 --> 00:12:46.649
“gods are lies”, he says, and “Men are
meat” – by breaking the laws of gods and

00:12:46.649 --> 00:12:49.280
men, Euron feels like a god himself.

00:12:49.280 --> 00:12:55.980
So Euron constantly mocks and perverts everything
that people believe in – he kinslays, blasphemes,

00:12:55.980 --> 00:12:59.180
breaks every taboo just cause he can.

00:12:59.180 --> 00:13:03.690
It turns out that the reason why Aeron is
so afraid of Euron is that when they were

00:13:03.690 --> 00:13:06.320
young, Euron sexually abused him.

00:13:06.320 --> 00:13:12.330
Euron says he taught Aeron how to pray, cause
Aeron would pray in terror when Euron came

00:13:12.330 --> 00:13:14.490
to “visit” in the night.

00:13:14.490 --> 00:13:18.630
Euron learned that sadistic cruelty gets him
worship.

00:13:18.630 --> 00:13:24.230
When he terrorises the east in the Silence,
murdering and raping, men “pray”.

00:13:24.230 --> 00:13:29.090
And so, Euron says, he is ”the godliest
man ever to raise sail”.

00:13:29.090 --> 00:13:33.740
If “All gods are lies”, Euron decides
to become his own god.

00:13:33.740 --> 00:13:37.550
And to become a god, he needs blood.

00:13:37.550 --> 00:13:42.560
The Forsaken is a chapter from the upcoming
Winds of Winter, read at a convention by George

00:13:42.560 --> 00:13:48.160
Martin – and it’s one of the darkest most
terrifying chapters in the series.

00:13:48.160 --> 00:13:52.730
Euron imprisons Aeron, and tortures him physically
and psychologically.

00:13:52.730 --> 00:13:57.560
He forces him to drink shade of the evening,
and Aeron has nightmarish visions of dead

00:13:57.560 --> 00:14:00.230
brothers and dead gods.

00:14:00.230 --> 00:14:06.140
Euron appears and says “These are the last
days, when the world shall be broken and remade.

00:14:06.140 --> 00:14:10.950
A new god shall be born from the graves and
charnel pits”.

00:14:10.950 --> 00:14:17.800
Euron’s hidden “blood eye” is finally
revealed, in all its horror and ambition – “I

00:14:17.800 --> 00:14:19.510
am your king”, he says.

00:14:19.510 --> 00:14:21.880
“I am your god”.

00:14:21.880 --> 00:14:26.180
After the vision, we see Euron imprisoning
priests of all different religions – as

00:14:26.180 --> 00:14:30.200
well as Aeron, he has priests of the Seven,
with their tongues ripped out.

00:14:30.200 --> 00:14:32.990
He has a red priest, with a burned-off face.

00:14:32.990 --> 00:14:35.529
He rips the legs off a warlock.

00:14:35.529 --> 00:14:41.519
And he has this girl Falia – Euron seduces
her, and impregnates her, and says she’ll

00:14:41.519 --> 00:14:47.260
be his wife, and she’s happy and excited,
but then Euron rips out her tongue.

00:14:47.260 --> 00:14:52.959
Euron ties Falia and Aeron and the priests
to the front of his ships, as Euron and the

00:14:52.959 --> 00:14:56.360
ironborn sail into battle against an enemy
fleet.

00:14:56.360 --> 00:15:02.640
“blood is power” – in this world there’s
magic in death and sacrifice – so Euron

00:15:02.640 --> 00:15:06.960
plans a blasphemous massacre of unimaginable
scale.

00:15:06.960 --> 00:15:11.730
This battle will kill his imprisoned priests,
and his brother, and kill Falia and their

00:15:11.730 --> 00:15:18.589
unborn child, it’ll kill the enemy fleet,
and his own fleet in a catastrophic orgy of

00:15:18.589 --> 00:15:25.830
death – Aeron dreams of ironborn ships “burning
on a boiling blood-red sea”.

00:15:25.830 --> 00:15:31.019
This carnage might “summon krakens from
the deep” – In Aeron’s vision, krakens

00:15:31.019 --> 00:15:33.100
come at Euron’s command.

00:15:33.100 --> 00:15:37.340
And we’re told that krakens can be drawn
to the water’s surface by blood – these

00:15:37.340 --> 00:15:40.550
visions show a blood-red sea.

00:15:40.550 --> 00:15:44.210
But Euron wants this massacre to make him
a god.

00:15:44.210 --> 00:15:48.140
He knows that death and fear give him power
and prayers.

00:15:48.140 --> 00:15:52.420
He knows there’s magic in the “holy blood”
of priests, and in the king’s blood of his

00:15:52.420 --> 00:15:54.130
unborn child.

00:15:54.130 --> 00:16:00.519
This battle is a giant blood magic ritual
– Euron will gorge on the deaths of thousands,

00:16:00.519 --> 00:16:06.709
to transform into a terrible godlike being
– Moqorro sees “A tall and twisted thing

00:16:06.709 --> 00:16:12.529
with one black eye and ten long arms, sailing
on a sea of blood”.

00:16:12.529 --> 00:16:18.540
Aeron sees Euron as “no longer human”,
“more squid than man”, “his face a mass

00:16:18.540 --> 00:16:22.850
of writhing tentacles” – so basically
Cthulhu.

00:16:22.850 --> 00:16:28.450
Maybe the Drowned God that the ironborn worship
is actually an eldritch monster, and Euron’s

00:16:28.450 --> 00:16:32.190
blood sacrifice will wake it from ageless
slumber.

00:16:32.190 --> 00:16:37.700
Or maybe Euron really did throw that dragon
egg into the sea, and all this magic blood

00:16:37.700 --> 00:16:41.420
will make it hatch into a monstrous sea dragon.

00:16:41.420 --> 00:16:47.149
There is all sorts of crazy scary imagery
here, and it’s not clear what exactly will

00:16:47.149 --> 00:16:52.970
happen – but there will be death and horror
and blood which Euron thinks will give him

00:16:52.970 --> 00:16:57.620
the godlike power to break and remake the
world.

00:16:57.620 --> 00:17:02.260
And it’s hinted that he’ll use this power
against the city of Oldtown.

00:17:02.260 --> 00:17:07.989
Euron’s close to Oldtown now, and his ironborn
have been raiding towards the city.

00:17:07.989 --> 00:17:13.179
Melisandre has a vision of “towers by the
sea, submerged beneath a black and bloody

00:17:13.179 --> 00:17:15.860
tide”, “rising from the depths”.

00:17:15.860 --> 00:17:21.389
It makes sense that Euron would want Oldtown,
because it’s full of secret magic.

00:17:21.389 --> 00:17:26.499
Oldtown’s Hightower is built on an ancient
foundation of strange black stone, which some

00:17:26.499 --> 00:17:32.609
say was built by a Lovecraftian fish people
called Deep Ones, which connects to the Cthulhu

00:17:32.609 --> 00:17:33.609
stuff.

00:17:33.609 --> 00:17:38.720
Oldtown has the Citadel, the university of
the maesters, which holds magic Valyrian artefacts

00:17:38.720 --> 00:17:40.590
called glass candles.

00:17:40.590 --> 00:17:45.669
A Faceless Man just infiltrated the Citadel,
possibly searching for a secret “blood-soaked

00:17:45.669 --> 00:17:48.580
tome” called “The Death of Dragons”.

00:17:48.580 --> 00:17:53.510
The city is ruled by Leyton Hightower and
his Mad Maid, who for the last ten years have

00:17:53.510 --> 00:17:58.850
stayed in the Hightower, “consulting books
of spells”, possibly to “raise an army

00:17:58.850 --> 00:18:00.649
from the deep”.

00:18:00.649 --> 00:18:07.469
Oldtown is a powder-keg of dormant magic powers
just waiting to explode into an eldritch clusterfuck

00:18:07.469 --> 00:18:14.129
– and Euron’s coming for it with a lit
match, “sailing on a sea of blood”.

00:18:14.129 --> 00:18:22.749
And the most dangerous power in Oldtown, the
one that could spark apocalypse, might be

00:18:22.749 --> 00:18:23.749
in the hands of Sam Tarly.

00:18:23.749 --> 00:18:28.130
In the books, there are legends of the Horn
of Winter, an ancient artefact with the power

00:18:28.130 --> 00:18:29.859
to destroy the Wall.

00:18:29.859 --> 00:18:33.470
Mance Rayder claims to have the Horn, but
that turns out to be fake.

00:18:33.470 --> 00:18:36.090
So “where is the true horn?”

00:18:36.090 --> 00:18:38.900
In Book 2, Jon finds an old horn.

00:18:38.900 --> 00:18:41.789
He gives it to Sam, who takes it to Oldtown.

00:18:41.789 --> 00:18:46.450
Sam and Jon don’t think this horn’s important,
but the books keep subtly reminding us that

00:18:46.450 --> 00:18:47.809
Sam has it.

00:18:47.809 --> 00:18:53.809
So fans suspect that Sam’s horn at Oldtown
is the Horn of Winter, with the power to bring

00:18:53.809 --> 00:18:57.340
down the Wall, and let the white walkers in.

00:18:57.340 --> 00:19:02.799
Euron might want the white walker apocalypse
– he says wants to break the world, and

00:19:02.799 --> 00:19:06.320
the Forsaken chapter’s full of apocalyptic
imagery.

00:19:06.320 --> 00:19:10.609
Euron may have learned about the white walkers
in his flying dream, just like when Bran sees

00:19:10.609 --> 00:19:13.190
“the heart of winter” “at the end of
the world”.

00:19:13.190 --> 00:19:18.799
It’s said the white walkers will bring a
Long Night that never ends.

00:19:18.799 --> 00:19:23.980
And Euron’s often described in terms of
night and darkness – his hair is black as

00:19:23.980 --> 00:19:29.559
a “midnight sea”, his sails are black
as a “starless sky”, he says “we shall

00:19:29.559 --> 00:19:32.419
feast before the fall of night”.

00:19:32.419 --> 00:19:38.020
At the kingsmoot, Euron’s dragon horn sounds
three times – at the Night’s Watch, three

00:19:38.020 --> 00:19:42.030
horn blasts means white walkers are coming.

00:19:42.030 --> 00:19:46.279
Euron may be the harbinger of apocalypse.

00:19:46.279 --> 00:19:51.289
According to eastern legend, the first Long
Night was caused by the Bloodstone Emperor.

00:19:51.289 --> 00:19:55.720
And this ancient Emperor is very similar to
Euron.

00:19:55.720 --> 00:20:00.499
The Emperor murdered his older sibling to
take her throne – just like Euron murders

00:20:00.499 --> 00:20:02.169
Balon for his throne.

00:20:02.169 --> 00:20:07.169
The Emperor practiced “dark arts”, “torture”,
slavery, and cannibalism, just like Euron

00:20:07.169 --> 00:20:11.429
practices dark arts, torture, slavery and
cannibalism.

00:20:11.429 --> 00:20:16.519
The Emperor “cast down the true gods”,
like Euron mocks and attack the gods.

00:20:16.519 --> 00:20:21.269
And the Emperor worshipped a creepy black
stone – just like the ironborn throne, and

00:20:21.269 --> 00:20:26.759
the Hightower foundation, and the city of
Asshai are all made of creepy black stone.

00:20:26.759 --> 00:20:32.070
--The Bloodstone Emperor married a “tiger-woman”(?),
which might be kind of like Euron wanting

00:20:32.070 --> 00:20:35.119
to marry the dragon-woman Daenerys.

00:20:35.119 --> 00:20:40.940
The sister who the Emperor usurped was called
the Amethyst Empress, and as Euron points

00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:44.109
out, Daenerys’ “eyes are amethysts”.

00:20:44.109 --> 00:20:49.929
Euron’s hidden eye is called his “blood
eye”, which fits with the Bloodstone Emperor.

00:20:49.929 --> 00:20:55.350
So there are lots of strong connections between
Euron and the Bloodstone Emperor, the guy

00:20:55.350 --> 00:20:59.830
who caused the first Long Night, when the
walkers came for the first time.

00:20:59.830 --> 00:21:03.049
It’s all happening again.

00:21:03.049 --> 00:21:09.239
Rodrik the Reader warns that “history is
a wheel”, and “What has happened before

00:21:09.239 --> 00:21:11.440
will … happen again”.

00:21:11.440 --> 00:21:17.149
Euron is the Bloodstone Emperor reborn, a
figure so addicted to power and blasphemy

00:21:17.149 --> 00:21:20.259
that he’ll bring darkness to the world.

00:21:20.259 --> 00:21:25.409
Fan theorist Poor Quentyn writes that Euron
will climb the Hightower in Oldtown – another

00:21:25.409 --> 00:21:30.830
“tall tower” – and will sound the Horn
of Winter, breaking the Wall, bringing the

00:21:30.830 --> 00:21:33.830
Night, and sparking the apocalypse.

00:21:33.830 --> 00:21:37.690
And after the storm, there’ll be silence.

00:21:37.690 --> 00:21:43.100
The Game of Thrones book series is called
A Song of Ice and Fire – lots of Martin’s

00:21:43.100 --> 00:21:48.999
stories are named after songs, because songs
to him represent life and love and memory.

00:21:48.999 --> 00:21:53.610
Euron represents the opposite of a song – he
is silence.

00:21:53.610 --> 00:21:58.860
His ship is named Silence, he makes people
mutes, he silences his brothers with shame,

00:21:58.860 --> 00:22:00.559
trauma and murder.

00:22:00.559 --> 00:22:06.249
He brings literal silence – the first time
he enters the story, “a sudden silence”

00:22:06.249 --> 00:22:09.529
falls, and when he leaves, silence lingers.

00:22:09.529 --> 00:22:16.049
Euron’s apocalyptic ambitions threaten to
silence the song of ice and fire itself.

00:22:16.049 --> 00:22:22.240
And sure, the white walkers are the true danger
– but it’s Euron who’ll unleash them.

00:22:22.240 --> 00:22:26.330
Which means the white walkers aren’t just
a magical fantasy threat – it’s more like

00:22:26.330 --> 00:22:30.679
climate change, a threat that humans bring
onto themselves.

00:22:30.679 --> 00:22:35.929
Book 2 and Book 3 in the series are called
A Clash of Kings and A Storm of Swords, because

00:22:35.929 --> 00:22:40.960
they’re about war – five kings fight to
control Westeros, and thousands of people

00:22:40.960 --> 00:22:42.029
die for them.

00:22:42.029 --> 00:22:47.470
But all of these kings die or fail, so what
did the war achieve?

00:22:47.470 --> 00:22:52.950
Book 4 explores the aftermath of war, and
it’s called A Feast for Crows – cause

00:22:52.950 --> 00:22:58.429
in the end, the only people who benefit from
all the death and chaos are the outlaws and

00:22:58.429 --> 00:23:03.379
opportunists, the monsters and betrayers who
exploit the war for their own gain – like

00:23:03.379 --> 00:23:06.999
crows feasting on the corpse of Westeros.

00:23:06.999 --> 00:23:12.980
The Bloody Mummers raid and rape, Lady Stoneheart
murders for vengeance, Littlefinger and the

00:23:12.980 --> 00:23:17.380
Boltons take over kingdoms – and Euron Greyjoy
arises.

00:23:17.380 --> 00:23:20.840
“Westeros is dying”, he says.

00:23:20.840 --> 00:23:25.669
“Those who follow me shall feast until the
end of their days”.

00:23:25.669 --> 00:23:31.210
Euron Crow’s Eye is the Crow of the book’s
title – an embodiment of all of the greed

00:23:31.210 --> 00:23:34.870
cruelty and pride that drives all the conflict
of the series.

00:23:34.870 --> 00:23:41.249
Cause like any politician, Euron isn’t dangerous
by himself – we never see him swing a sword,

00:23:41.249 --> 00:23:43.669
or cast a spell, [he just takes drugs and
talks shit].

00:23:43.669 --> 00:23:47.950
Euron’s powerful because people are scared
and ignorant and greedy enough to follow him

00:23:47.950 --> 00:23:53.479
– the people chose him at the kingsmoot,
the dark lord was democratically elected.

00:23:53.479 --> 00:24:00.159
His evil is our evil, his power comes from
the fear hope and hate inside of us – that’s

00:24:00.159 --> 00:24:06.669
how he manipulates his family, his people,
and the world, that’s how Westeros is reduced

00:24:06.669 --> 00:24:09.070
to corpses and crows.

00:24:09.070 --> 00:24:14.139
So Euron’s story isn’t just about dragons
and krakens – though those bits will be

00:24:14.139 --> 00:24:20.049
fucken sick – it’s also about how real
human impulses lead us all into self-destruction,

00:24:20.049 --> 00:24:23.789
and silence.

00:24:23.789 --> 00:24:29.299
So tl;dr, that goofy pirate on the dragon
show who talks about fingers in bums is actually

00:24:29.299 --> 00:24:36.330
the most scary smart magical mysterious evil
motherfucker in Westeros – but we’ll have

00:24:36.330 --> 00:24:39.249
to wait for the next book to see what happens
next.

00:24:39.249 --> 00:24:40.249
George pls.

00:24:40.249 --> 00:24:41.249
Come on George.

00:24:41.249 --> 00:24:44.950
If you wanna truly appreciate the message
and mysteries of this story, you’ve got

00:24:44.950 --> 00:24:46.599
to check out the books.

00:24:46.599 --> 00:24:50.210
As well as the main series, there’s the
worldbook, and Fire and Blood, and the Dunk

00:24:50.210 --> 00:24:54.879
and Egg stories – and you can get any one
of these on audiobook for free right now by

00:24:54.879 --> 00:24:57.309
signing up for a trial with Audible.

00:24:57.309 --> 00:25:01.830
Members get an audiobook each month, and if
you cancel, you keep the audiobooks.

